1
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:42,480
It's because that's what you think!
That's why you adopted Rin,

2
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:45,880
despite killing her father
and your own senior!

3
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:47,800
<i>Techut's fingerprint is on here.</i>

4
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:50,440
<i>Hurry and collect it,</i>
<i>so we can enter the lab.</i>

5
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:55,880
‪-Hey!
‪-Oh no!

6
00:02:55,960 --> 00:02:57,720
Don't let Taiga out of the 3C building.

7
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:02,000
Why are you so nice to me?

8
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:04,000
We'll have to kill each other eventually.

9
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:22,600
So you just invited yourself over?

10
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,840
While you're here,
can I ask you something?

11
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,240
Sure.

12
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:31,760
So 3C-coins can be used to buy anything,

13
00:03:32,640 --> 00:03:35,280
both legal and illegal stuff, right?

14
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,160
Yeah.

15
00:03:37,760 --> 00:03:41,520
So if we have those coins
in our crypto account, we can buy stuff?

16
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,440
Yes.

17
00:03:44,480 --> 00:03:46,440
The purchases cannot be traced either.

18
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,720
Then they can also be hacked.

19
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:52,800
What are you trying to do, Aru?

20
00:03:53,480 --> 00:03:56,520
Can you teach me how to trade crypto?
I want to get rich fast.

21
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,960
You'll teach me, right?

22
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,240
Sure,

23
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:09,960
but there's a risk
in all kinds of investment, Aru.

24
00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:12,200
You have to remember that investment

25
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:15,760
is the competition between greed and fear,

26
00:04:16,959 --> 00:04:20,079
just like how every coin has two sides.

27
00:04:20,880 --> 00:04:22,960
Or another good metaphor

28
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:26,480
is how you can use knives to cook,

29
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,080
but at the same time,

30
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:30,960
you can also use them to kill people.

31
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:35,880
Get it?

32
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,040
Yeah.

33
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:51,880
Thank you for rushing here, Mr. Taiga.

34
00:04:51,960 --> 00:04:54,040
I may work spontaneously,

35
00:04:54,560 --> 00:04:56,680
but I never avoid my responsibilities.

36
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,960
If our principles clash,

37
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,720
I'll have to quit this job.

38
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:06,800
You don't have to.

39
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:10,920
3C still wants to enter
challenging markets.

40
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:15,720
You know, I still remember
what we talked about.

41
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:19,920
Yes,

42
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,520
it takes three things to do marketing.

43
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:27,400
The brain, the heart, and sex.

44
00:05:28,840 --> 00:05:32,880
The hardest thing to win over
is the heart.

45
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:38,080
That's why 3C
needs your good ideas, Mr. Taiga.

46
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:40,520
It's so we can win over people's hearts.

47
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:42,520
I really appreciate it, Ms. Nun.

48
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,800
I feel like I have a lot of freedom
working for you.

49
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,640
I feel very at ease.

50
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:40,840
Rin needs to stay here until she recovers.

51
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:44,680
Once you go back to 3C,
you'll face a lot more problems.

52
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:47,640
Who knows when we'll even find
the leader of Fire Phoenix.

53
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,800
I need to be there to help you.

54
00:06:50,960 --> 00:06:52,240
It's okay, Khanin.

55
00:06:53,280 --> 00:06:55,080
I can take care of myself.

56
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,040
But…

57
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,600
Rin needs someone to take care of her.

58
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:06,240
I want to leave Rin…

59
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:11,920
in the care of the one I trust the most.

60
00:07:13,120 --> 00:07:15,280
I'm only here because of Taiga,

61
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,400
not you.

62
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:32,640
If Rin wants to quit,
what does she need to do?

63
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,960
Since when did you become Rin's new boss?

64
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:46,120
I want Rin to work with me.

65
00:07:47,520 --> 00:07:49,080
Have Rin tell me herself.

66
00:07:50,560 --> 00:07:52,040
She won't be able to come for now.

67
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:56,600
You can go to jail
for false imprisonment, Mr. Taiga.

68
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,360
Actually,

69
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:03,360
it's more like she's under protection.

70
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:08,720
Why would she need your protection?

71
00:08:09,320 --> 00:08:10,760
I bet you know why.

72
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:13,960
This is 3C.

73
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,880
I own this place.

74
00:08:15,960 --> 00:08:17,920
Rin works for me.

75
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,360
Have her contact me herself.

76
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:24,680
What's she doing? Where is she?
Why would she need your protection?

77
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,480
If she can explain it,

78
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:29,840
then I'll let her stay
wherever she's supposed to.

79
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,800
This is Rin speaking, Mr. Naruban.

80
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,280
How are you?

81
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,880
I failed in my duties.

82
00:09:23,040 --> 00:09:24,720
I was out of line.

83
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,760
I just up and disappeared.

84
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,360
I'd like to quit.

85
00:09:34,080 --> 00:09:35,320
At least you feel guilty.

86
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:38,920
<i>I'm sure you have your personal reasons.</i>

87
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:42,760
You don't have to quit yet.
You may take some time off.

88
00:09:44,800 --> 00:09:46,080
Thank you.

89
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:54,080
Once you recover,
come and apologize to me in person.

90
00:09:56,880 --> 00:09:57,920
Understood.

91
00:10:07,680 --> 00:10:10,840
You're giving her time off
without telling HR.

92
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,440
Why?

93
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:15,200
You've never given anyone
this kind of privilege.

94
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:18,120
Can't I make any changes?

95
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:27,440
This is not the way I want you to change.

96
00:10:30,280 --> 00:10:32,960
You know I'd never do what you want.

97
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,600
Why?

98
00:10:36,280 --> 00:10:38,920
Is it so hard to do something for me?

99
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:44,240
It's the last thing I'd do
for an insatiable wife like you.

100
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,480
Cuss me out all you want,

101
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,240
but I really want you to know

102
00:11:08,160 --> 00:11:10,080
that I love you the most.

103
00:11:12,560 --> 00:11:13,880
I'm sorry.

104
00:11:16,040 --> 00:11:17,600
Please forgive me.

105
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:29,080
So,

106
00:11:29,840 --> 00:11:31,520
you never loved me, did you?

107
00:11:34,240 --> 00:11:35,720
I used to love you,

108
00:11:36,440 --> 00:11:38,080
until I saw you buying

109
00:11:38,160 --> 00:11:41,800
that very rare, limited-edition watch
the day before my birthday.

110
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,160
I thought it'd be a gift from my wife,

111
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:46,720
but no.

112
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:50,360
That watch ended up on the wrist
of another man.

113
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:53,200
The man who had a business deal with 3C.

114
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,120
The man who's Nunnapat's real father.

115
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:58,800
Well, you never took care of me.
You left me all alone--

116
00:11:58,880 --> 00:12:01,600
No matter how lonely you feel,
you can't cheat on your husband!

117
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:06,400
I won't stand looking like a cuck
because I'm a lousy husband.

118
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:08,440
Just let everyone know

119
00:12:08,520 --> 00:12:12,120
you're an evil, good-for-nothing wife
who sleeps around,

120
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,840
but I need to look like
the best husband and father ever.

121
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:16,400
You're a selfish jerk!

122
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:19,160
Yes, I am. So what?

123
00:12:20,200 --> 00:12:22,480
You're just one of my assets.

124
00:12:23,280 --> 00:12:26,400
Forget putting on your wings
and flying away to find happiness.

125
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,960
You deserve to die painfully
in this cage, Giranun.

126
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:04,280
Aru. Rin.

127
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,760
Want some? The locals here gave us this.

128
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:07,920
Huh?

129
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,400
Wow.

130
00:13:13,160 --> 00:13:14,480
Is it good?

131
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:27,960
Feel free to chat with your friends,
but make it quick.

132
00:13:28,680 --> 00:13:31,600
It gets cold quickly around here.
You'll recover more slowly.

133
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:35,480
I'll be around. Call me if you need me.

134
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,360
You know,

135
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,440
he's as aggressive as a dog.

136
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,600
So, who is he?

137
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,440
Khanin, a friend of Taiga's.

138
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,640
How did you two get here?

139
00:13:56,760 --> 00:13:58,960
Sun and I swapped shifts
with our coworkers.

140
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:02,480
I was worried. I wanted
to see you with my own eyes.

141
00:14:03,080 --> 00:14:05,880
Thank you so much.
I'll go back as soon as possible.

142
00:14:06,520 --> 00:14:09,160
You don't need to.
Stay and recover a little longer.

143
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,600
You look so exhausted,

144
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:15,840
and who knows if the cure
gave you any side effects.

145
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,280
Everything's still in a trial phase.

146
00:14:19,240 --> 00:14:20,320
Yeah.

147
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:22,320
Take care of Aru for me.

148
00:14:23,120 --> 00:14:26,560
Don't worry.
I'll take care of her as well as I can.

149
00:14:30,680 --> 00:14:33,280
- Take care, okay?
- Sure.

150
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:46,960
ARU

151
00:15:48,760 --> 00:15:50,120
My friends already left.

152
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:53,040
Thank you for letting me see them.

153
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,040
Rin.

154
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:03,880
Can I ask you something?

155
00:16:07,160 --> 00:16:09,160
Do you know Inspector Phumin?

156
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:13,400
Hm.

157
00:16:13,920 --> 00:16:16,680
Not really. Why do you ask?

158
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:20,800
I was just wondering about something.

159
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:22,440
But if you don't know him, that's okay.

160
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,920
Why'd you stop here?

161
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,800
We need to talk, Aru.

162
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:58,680
Can we talk at home?

163
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:01,760
No. We have to talk right here, right now.

164
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,400
If you're gonna act this way,

165
00:17:05,000 --> 00:17:06,400
I'm going home myself.

166
00:17:13,200 --> 00:17:14,280
Sun.

167
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,800
What are you doing?

168
00:17:30,160 --> 00:17:33,600
Aru. Aru!

169
00:18:16,640 --> 00:18:20,200
TECHUT: DON'T FORGET TO SEND ME THE VIDEO
OR YOUR MOM AND SISTER ARE DEAD. GOT IT?

170
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:23,880
Good. Whoever betrays me
needs to die a slow and painful death.

171
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,440
What are you smiling about?

172
00:20:28,520 --> 00:20:29,920
Did the coin prices go up?

173
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:33,240
Just use your brain
for shopping and spending money, Mom.

174
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:35,240
Leave the difficult things to me and Dad.

175
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,960
Your dearest family.

176
00:21:26,960 --> 00:21:28,920
I really like people like you.

177
00:21:29,440 --> 00:21:32,440
A family person. You're malleable.

178
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:37,600
You know Aru, right?

179
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:42,560
No, I don't.

180
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:44,640
If you lie to me,

181
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:48,080
you'll be seeing a video of my men
killing your mom and sister!

182
00:21:49,160 --> 00:21:50,080
You're an animal!

183
00:21:50,160 --> 00:21:53,720
You're an animal too.
You're my obedient pet.

184
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,520
You will do everything I say.

185
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:58,600
Got it?

186
00:22:33,920 --> 00:22:34,920
Aru.

187
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,040
It's late. What are you doing out here?

188
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:58,440
I can't sleep. I miss my friends.

189
00:22:58,960 --> 00:23:00,440
Your friends were just here.

190
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:03,440
I don't know.

191
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:05,720
I suddenly miss them.

192
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:09,840
Maybe I'm too worried about them.

193
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,280
I bet you understand.
I'm sure you have friends too.

194
00:23:23,440 --> 00:23:26,400
I used to, but that was long ago.

195
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,520
- What about now?
- I have none.

196
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:34,240
- What about your family?
- None. Let me ask you too.

197
00:23:36,280 --> 00:23:38,360
I have friends, as you saw.

198
00:23:39,960 --> 00:23:41,080
And your family?

199
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,120
None. Just like you.

200
00:23:46,640 --> 00:23:50,920
Everyone has a family, though.

201
00:23:53,760 --> 00:23:57,480
Then tell me about yours. I'm waiting.

202
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,400
I had a dad,

203
00:24:06,400 --> 00:24:08,640
a mom, and a younger sister.

204
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:11,720
They're all dead.

205
00:24:13,120 --> 00:24:14,120
What about you?

206
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:18,440
I never said
I'd tell you my story in exchange.

207
00:24:19,120 --> 00:24:22,000
That's not fair. Do you not trust me?

208
00:24:22,520 --> 00:24:24,960
Trust cannot be proven by words alone.

209
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:27,640
I already know you don't trust me,

210
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:31,480
so no matter what I tell you,
you won't buy it so easily.

211
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:33,240
You're both still up?

212
00:24:36,120 --> 00:24:37,520
We were just talking.

213
00:24:37,600 --> 00:24:38,680
Ah.

214
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:41,080
It's kind of pretty here at night too.

215
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:44,600
Aren't you scared?

216
00:24:45,200 --> 00:24:47,200
Some women are afraid of the dark.

217
00:24:51,120 --> 00:24:52,360
I'm not.

218
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:57,240
Being out in the light too much
can be dangerous too.

219
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:00,000
Yes.

220
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,240
Please take care of your health, Ms. Rin.

221
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,800
If you'll excuse me.

222
00:25:05,320 --> 00:25:06,720
Good night.

223
00:25:17,360 --> 00:25:18,960
I'm not sleepy yet.

224
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:21,560
No worries at all.

225
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,440
Aru won't pick up.

226
00:25:44,480 --> 00:25:46,680
INCOMING CALL - DHAMMATAT - MOBILE

227
00:25:51,160 --> 00:25:53,720
She hasn't picked up
since she left Inseethong Farm.

228
00:25:59,240 --> 00:26:00,760
Sun went with her, didn't he?

229
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:06,840
Maybe they just want
some alone time together

230
00:26:07,600 --> 00:26:08,720
to talk,

231
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:11,840
sleep together,

232
00:26:12,440 --> 00:26:14,760
and sleep in together.

233
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:20,720
Didn't I make you feel fuzzy at all?

234
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:26,360
We should assume the worst.

235
00:26:26,440 --> 00:26:29,680
Aru isn't obsessed with romance like you.

236
00:26:30,280 --> 00:26:31,200
How do you know that?

237
00:26:32,320 --> 00:26:36,320
I know everything on earth.
It's just that I may or may not tell you.

238
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:41,120
I'm not talking about information,
but rather feelings.

239
00:26:41,200 --> 00:26:43,280
Feelings. Got it?

240
00:26:44,680 --> 00:26:45,840
Yes.

241
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:47,520
Aru is here.

242
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:54,760
That's in Bangkok.
And not her old house either.

243
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:56,080
Where's that?

244
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,080
I don't know either.

245
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:02,680
You can hack CCTV cameras, can't you?

246
00:27:02,760 --> 00:27:04,280
Don't be silly.

247
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:07,200
I'm not that kind of person.

248
00:27:09,840 --> 00:27:11,520
There. I did it.

249
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:17,600
Whose house is that?
Why'd she go there without telling us?

250
00:27:24,040 --> 00:27:26,080
One hot americano, please.

251
00:27:27,360 --> 00:27:28,480
Here you go.

252
00:27:34,640 --> 00:27:35,840
Please have a seat.

253
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:41,400
Thank you.

254
00:27:44,800 --> 00:27:46,400
Is Aru with Rin right now, Sun?

255
00:27:51,320 --> 00:27:52,440
Or is she with you?

256
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:58,800
I'll only ask once.
I don't like asking twice.

257
00:28:23,800 --> 00:28:25,160
She's not with me.

258
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:12,720
Why are you in my office?

259
00:29:31,160 --> 00:29:33,160
This building's got
security cameras everywhere.

260
00:29:53,920 --> 00:29:55,760
If you didn't betray me,

261
00:29:57,040 --> 00:29:59,320
your life would've been better, Aru.

262
00:30:02,200 --> 00:30:04,560
I was going to buy you a house,

263
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:07,400
and once I get tired of you,

264
00:30:08,600 --> 00:30:11,360
I'd take you to my friend,
so he can have a try too.

265
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,240
It's green!

266
00:30:35,360 --> 00:30:36,360
Profit!

267
00:30:38,200 --> 00:30:39,480
I made a profit!

268
00:30:41,680 --> 00:30:44,040
Long live 3C-Coin!

269
00:31:00,560 --> 00:31:01,600
It's pretty.

270
00:31:06,240 --> 00:31:07,760
Would you like to try it on?

271
00:31:09,120 --> 00:31:10,080
Sure.

272
00:31:11,160 --> 00:31:12,280
Take her.

273
00:31:33,080 --> 00:31:33,960
Please try these on.

274
00:32:03,200 --> 00:32:04,280
Excuse me.

275
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:50,680
Try walking in it.

276
00:32:51,840 --> 00:32:52,920
Okay.

277
00:33:06,640 --> 00:33:07,560
What do you think?

278
00:33:08,160 --> 00:33:09,240
You look very pretty.

279
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:39,440
I'll do another experiment
at Uncle Narumit's farm.

280
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:43,720
You'll be shocked to see
how fast our virus can kill.

281
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:48,960
Maybe six months, one month,

282
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:50,760
or instant death.

283
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,520
Hold off on the experiment.

284
00:33:55,640 --> 00:33:57,720
- Dad.
- Listen to me.

285
00:33:58,240 --> 00:34:01,520
If you keep getting people sick or killed,

286
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:05,640
Indhorn will catch on to you, and the farm
will no longer be safe for you.

287
00:34:05,720 --> 00:34:08,199
Government officials
will storm it to investigate.

288
00:34:08,280 --> 00:34:10,560
Then we can do the experiment
in the basement here.

289
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,480
Hey.

290
00:34:13,199 --> 00:34:16,400
You want us to fall apart
and go to jail or something?

291
00:34:21,239 --> 00:34:22,560
How will we fall apart, Dad?

292
00:34:22,639 --> 00:34:26,600
We're well-connected. All the police
and prosecutors are your people.

293
00:34:27,639 --> 00:34:29,600
Some bodies aren't so easy to hide.

294
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:30,760
Then don't.

295
00:34:31,280 --> 00:34:32,760
Grind all their flesh and bones.

296
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:35,120
Dump them in the ocean.
There won't be any DNA left.

297
00:34:35,199 --> 00:34:38,719
I'm ordering you, so do as I say.
Pause the experiment with the people.

298
00:34:39,400 --> 00:34:42,719
People who want to thrive
aren't afraid of silly stuff like this.

299
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:48,080
If I'd been as reckless as you,
I wouldn't have lived to this day.

300
00:34:48,639 --> 00:34:51,000
Hold off on the experiment. Just wait!

301
00:35:32,120 --> 00:35:33,160
Why are you out here?

302
00:35:36,240 --> 00:35:37,400
I wanted to go for a walk.

303
00:35:39,360 --> 00:35:40,680
Are you all better now?

304
00:35:42,760 --> 00:35:43,760
I'm doing fine.

305
00:35:45,080 --> 00:35:48,240
You're lying. You're not fine.

306
00:35:51,680 --> 00:35:53,200
I promised Taiga

307
00:35:53,720 --> 00:35:57,560
to take care of you for him,
so I have to do it.

308
00:36:02,280 --> 00:36:03,520
Don't force yourself.

309
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:10,560
Sometimes we have to force ourselves
to do what we don't want to.

310
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,440
I want to kill you,

311
00:36:18,040 --> 00:36:19,680
yet I have to take care of you.

312
00:36:21,120 --> 00:36:22,520
Well, here's your chance.

313
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:24,160
Don't challenge me, Rin.

314
00:36:25,560 --> 00:36:26,720
I'm only holding back

315
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:29,640
for Taiga's sake. I feel bad for him.

316
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:32,080
Throughout Taiga's life,

317
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,440
too many cruel things
have happened to him.

318
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:37,640
He's been lonely long enough.

319
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:42,200
He shouldn't have to be betrayed
by someone close to him too.

320
00:36:55,040 --> 00:36:56,760
Rin, Rin!

321
00:36:58,640 --> 00:36:59,680
Sit down.

322
00:37:02,080 --> 00:37:03,400
Why are you bleeding?

323
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,040
I'm fine.

324
00:37:10,600 --> 00:37:12,280
You relapsed, didn't you?

325
00:37:18,280 --> 00:37:20,480
I was bleeding
out of my mouth this morning.

326
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:24,360
You must be happy I'm nearly dying.

327
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:28,520
But you won't die so easily.

328
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:33,120
Can you stay away from Taiga already?

329
00:37:34,520 --> 00:37:38,240
I never held anyone back,
and I don't have to run away from anyone.

330
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,960
Then listen carefully.

331
00:37:41,040 --> 00:37:43,680
Taiga would lose it all
just because he's worried about you,

332
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:46,520
yet you still don't know
how important your life is to him?

333
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:50,560
And if he still has to keep
protecting you like this,

334
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:52,440
he might even die

335
00:37:52,960 --> 00:37:55,600
before finding the person
who killed his family.

336
00:37:58,320 --> 00:37:59,480
And as for you,

337
00:38:00,760 --> 00:38:02,960
you have a goal in mind too, don't you?

338
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:07,720
That goal of yours
that you won't tell anyone.

339
00:38:11,960 --> 00:38:16,120
I won't look back anymore.
I'll only look forward.

340
00:38:16,200 --> 00:38:20,240
And my life goal is no one's business.
Not yours either.

341
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:23,240
You can go ahead
and tell Taiga to stay away from me

342
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:25,800
if you think forcing him
will make you feel better.

343
00:38:36,160 --> 00:38:37,880
- Who?
- Punlop.

344
00:38:39,160 --> 00:38:40,400
He followed you here.

345
00:38:41,680 --> 00:38:43,360
How did he know I'm here?

346
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:45,680
He's not stupid.

347
00:38:46,400 --> 00:38:48,920
He must've guessed
based on what's related to Naruban.

348
00:38:50,800 --> 00:38:51,880
Go hide.

349
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:39,720
Sharp nose, you mutt.

350
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:43,880
What a surprise to see you here.

351
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:45,880
You're the one who needs to tell me

352
00:39:46,560 --> 00:39:47,800
what you're doing here.

353
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:51,560
- I'd rather not.
- Tell me what the hell you're doing here!

354
00:39:57,320 --> 00:40:00,400
What about you? Hiding someone?

355
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:03,520
Ever since you wore your collar
and got a new owner,

356
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:05,800
you sure bite deep.

357
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:07,440
Well, at least

358
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:11,160
I'm not some cop
who threw his honor away in the trash,

359
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:15,280
who deceives, bends the truth,
and only thinks about his own benefit.

360
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:19,960
You really should've been dead
long ago, Punlop.

361
00:40:20,040 --> 00:40:22,200
Yet I survived every single time

362
00:40:23,640 --> 00:40:24,720
because I'm smarter than you.

363
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:39,520
What the hell?

364
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:55,920
When you die,
no one will cry for a guy like you.

365
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:59,240
And a guy like you should die already.

366
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:13,800
Go, go!

367
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,360
Damn you, Punlop!

368
00:41:26,720 --> 00:41:28,800
You need more people here.

369
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:30,800
This isn't just about Ms. Rin.

370
00:41:31,320 --> 00:41:34,760
You're too lax. At this rate,
anyone can do anything on your farm.

371
00:41:36,640 --> 00:41:37,800
Okay.

372
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:42,520
I'll have my workers tighten up security
where you and Ms. Rin are staying.

373
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:43,760
But where's Ms. Rin?

374
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:45,240
I'm safe.

375
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:51,280
Uncle Punlop didn't hurt you two, right?

376
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:54,240
That scumbag just won't die.

377
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:58,760
If he already got here once,
he won't stop there.

378
00:41:59,280 --> 00:42:01,640
When he suspects something,
he never lets it slide.

379
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:04,640
Mr. Indhorn,

380
00:42:05,480 --> 00:42:07,120
I shouldn't stay here.

381
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:09,720
I don't want any more trouble
for your farm.

382
00:42:12,320 --> 00:42:14,880
I can't let you leave my farm
and risk your life either.

383
00:42:14,960 --> 00:42:17,360
Here, you have me and Mr. Khanin.

384
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:19,440
You'll be safe for sure.

385
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:22,840
I'm really sorry.

386
00:42:28,120 --> 00:42:29,320
Get better soon.

387
00:42:30,800 --> 00:42:35,120
Once you do, we'll go face Punlop again.

388
00:43:03,680 --> 00:43:05,000
My virus.

389
00:43:13,480 --> 00:43:14,920
The cure and the vaccine

390
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,120
can only be bought by 3C-coins.

391
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:32,240
You did your job very well.

392
00:43:33,320 --> 00:43:36,520
Rest assured,
your mom and sister will be safe.

393
00:43:38,800 --> 00:43:39,800
Thank you.

394
00:43:46,160 --> 00:43:47,640
I have another job for you.

395
00:43:50,280 --> 00:43:51,680
I'm not killing anyone again.

396
00:43:53,320 --> 00:43:56,600
You won't have to.
And you're a pro at this job.

397
00:43:57,120 --> 00:44:01,200
Find a way to inflate 3C-Coin
so that I profit 100 million in two days.

398
00:44:02,440 --> 00:44:06,720
Then, I'll tell my men
to let your mom and sister go.

399
00:44:37,240 --> 00:44:38,680
Want to know who killed your father?

400
00:44:38,760 --> 00:44:41,360
Don't go. Uncle Punlop will kill you.

401
00:44:42,560 --> 00:44:44,440
I was just thinking about you,
my lovely niece.

402
00:44:45,400 --> 00:44:46,200
Rin!

403
00:44:46,880 --> 00:44:48,040
Help me.

404
00:44:48,120 --> 00:44:49,080
Who did this to you?

405
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:52,520
<i>Who's your boss, Uncle?</i>

406
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:54,080
Why ask about Damon out of the blue?

407
00:44:54,960 --> 00:44:55,760
Dad--

408
00:44:55,840 --> 00:44:58,200
Pok, help me! Please help my son.

409
00:44:58,280 --> 00:44:59,160
<i>Where are my brothers?</i>

410
00:45:00,400 --> 00:45:02,800
Where the hell are my brothers?!

411
00:45:30,680 --> 00:45:33,240
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
